Assignment 4
Apply internal, external, and inline CSS to style a web page with headings and tables.
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<title>CSS Types Demo</title>
<!-- 2. INTERNAL CSS -->
<style>
body {
background-color: #f0f8ff; /* AliceBlue */
font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;
}
/* Class Selector for Table */
.myTable {
border-collapse: collapse;
width: 80%;
margin: auto;
background-color: white;
box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
}
.myTable th {
background-color: #4CAF50;
color: white;
padding: 12px;
text-align: left;
}
.myTable td {
border: 1px solid #ddd;
padding: 8px;
}
/* Hover Effect */
.myTable tr:hover { background-color: #f5f5f5; }
</style>
</head>
<body>
<!-- 1. INLINE CSS -->
<h1 style="color: navy; text-align: center; border-bottom: 2px solid navy;">
CSS Implementation Demo
</h1>
<p style="text-align: center; color: gray; font-style: italic;">
This text is styled using Inline CSS.
</p>
<br>
<div align="center">
<h3>Employee Data Table (Styled via Internal CSS)</h3>
<table class="myTable">
<tr>
<th>ID</th>
<th>Name</th>
<th>Department</th>
<th>Status</th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>101</td>
<td>Alice Johnson</td>
<td>HR</td>
<td style="color: green; font-weight: bold;">Active</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>102</td>
<td>Bob Smith</td>
<td>IT</td>
<td style="color: green; font-weight: bold;">Active</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>103</td>
<td>Charlie Brown</td>
<td>Finance</td>
<td style="color: red; font-weight: bold;">Inactive</td>
</tr>
</table>
</div>
</body>
</html>
